threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
Hi, i have this board no liquid spill, i have PP5V_S5 = 1,2V, in diode mode 0,447 (bad), i try to change U7501 but same problem. 
i don't understand where the PP5V_S5 is generated, by U7501?

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
Why do you think 447 is bad?
Doesn't look low at all.

Do you get SMC_PM_G2_EN and correct PPBUS_G3H?
Check 5V_S5 disconnecting trackpad flex.
If still bad, change U7501.
As last step, change U7400 if needed.

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
PPBUS=8,59V
SMC_PM_G2_EN=3,41
sorry i say bad for 1,2V  i have just the board with magsafe board and cable flex. 
i remove U7400 same problem, i change again u7501 and i come back

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
Same with another U7501 PP5V_S5 1,2V
i try to remove U7400 and L4820 but no change

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
I hope you didn't power up the board without U7400!!!

Remove C7505, C7410, C4810 and check again 5V_S5.

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
i power up the board without U7400, is it dangerous? because i haven't PP5V_S5. i dead the board?
I remove C7505, C7400 instead of C7410, C4810, same 1,2V on PP5V_S5

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
CPU could be fried now.
Post diode mode to ground at L7430.

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
Doesn't look bad, you could be lucky.

Check diode mode on all 3V3 and 5V power rails; from S5 to S0.
Check all traces, solders and components around U7501.

threads.message:

threads.title: 820-00165 Green led but not start
threads.message:
"22=4,57"
Are you really sure?
If yes, change U7501.
There is 3.3V LDO output...

ok thanks, i solve the problem, i think i remove by mistake C7503, when i change U7501 the first time.
Now the mac work well.
